		<div id="comment-486408">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/934fb5420743a56906fa20026886bd69?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/934fb5420743a56906fa20026886bd69?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://hot-issues.net' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Dan Kauffman</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>			</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
				
			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-486408">
				August 28, 2016 at 17:42					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>You need to edit this then</p>
<p>[material deleted]</p>
<p>What are the Hugo Awards?</p>
<p>The Hugo Awards, to give them their full title, are awards for excellence in the field of science fiction and fantasy. They were first awarded in 1953, and have been awarded every year since 1955. The awards are run by and voted on by fans.&#8221;</p>
<p>Just put in &#8220;members of Worldcon&#8221; instead of fans, Which of course explains why Toni Weiscoff was also below No Award.</p>
<p>Best Editor, Long Form (2,386 final ballots, 1764 nominating ballots)</p>
<p>Sheila E. Gilbert<br />
Liz Gorinsky<br />
No Award<br />
Toni Weisskopf<br />
Jim Minz<br />
Vox Day</p>
<p>Sorry but it looks like a lot of the tastes of the World Con members was more reflected by Lock Step Slate Voting to eliminate people for political reasons rather than their talents and work.</p>
</div>

